org.eclipse.gef4.mvc.fx.policies

Interface IFXOnDragPolicy

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAdaptable.Bound<IVisualPart<javafx.scene.Node,? extends javafx.scene.Node>>, IPolicy<javafx.scene.Node>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FXBendFirstAnchorageOnSegmentHandleDragPolicy, FXBendOnSegmentDragPolicy, FXMarqueeOnDragPolicy, FXNormalizeConnectedOnDragPolicy, FXResizeTransformSelectedOnHandleDragPolicy, FXResizeTranslateFirstAnchorageOnHandleDragPolicy, FXRotateSelectedOnHandleDragPolicy, FXTranslateSelectedOnDragPolicy

    public interface IFXOnDragPolicy
extends IPolicy<javafx.scene.Node>
    An interaction policy that implements the IFXOnDragPolicy interface will be notified about mouse press-drag-release events by the FXClickDragTool .

    • Method Detail

      • drag

        void drag(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent e,
          Dimension delta)
        This callback method is invoked when the mouse is moved while a button is pressed.
        Parameters:
        e - The original MouseEvent.
        delta - The mouse offset since press(MouseEvent) (in pixel).

      • dragAborted

        void dragAborted()
        This callback method is invoked when the mouse drag gesture is aborted, i.e. the gesture ends unexpectedly, without a mouse release event being fired. The policy can decide to commit or roll back its transaction. The execution transaction to which operations are added during a mouse drag gesture is closed after execution of this method.

      • hideIndicationCursor

        void hideIndicationCursor()
        Restores the original mouse cursor when it was previously changed by a call to showIndicationCursor(KeyEvent) or showIndicationCursor(MouseEvent).

      • press

        void press(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent e)
        This callback method is invoked when a mouse button is pressed on the host, which starts a mouse drag gesture. An execution transaction is opened prior to execution of this method to which all operations are added that are executed during a mouse drag gesture.
        Parameters:
        e - The original MouseEvent

      • release

        void release(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent e,
             Dimension delta)
        This callback method is invoked when the initially pressed mouse button is released, which ends the gesture. The execution transaction to which operations are added during a mouse drag gesture is closed after execution of this method.
        Parameters:
        e - The original MouseEvent.
        delta - The mouse offset since press(MouseEvent) (in pixel).

      • showIndicationCursor

        boolean showIndicationCursor(javafx.scene.input.KeyEvent event)
        Changes the mouse cursor depending on the given KeyEvent to indicate the action that is performed by this policy. The return value indicates if the mouse cursor was changed or not.
        Parameters:
        event - The KeyEvent that initiated the determination of an indication cursor.
        Returns:
        true if the mouse cursor was changed, otherwise false.

      • showIndicationCursor

        boolean showIndicationCursor(javafx.scene.input.MouseEvent event)
        Changes the mouse cursor depending on the given MouseEvent to indicate the action that is performed by this policy. The return value indicates if the mouse cursor was changed or not.
        Parameters:
        event - The MouseEvent that initiated the determination of an indication cursor.
        Returns:
        true if the mouse cursor was changed, otherwise false.
